<subSubSection id="C37219DAFFFD2012FF54FF62FC04FF19" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BD74A51FFFD2012FF54FF62FC04FF19" blockId="1.[151,1436,151,536]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">
<emphasis id="B91C9643FFFD2012FF54FF62FEADFF5E" bold="true" box="[199,334,152,176]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">Etymology.</emphasis>
We humbly dedicate this species to Her Royal Highness, The Princess Maha Chakri Sirindhorn of 
<collectingCountry id="F37F0AC1FFFD2012FF04FF46FF1EFF3B" box="[151,253,188,213]" name="Thailand" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">Thailand</collectingCountry>
, in recognition of her continuing support of nature conservation and as a mark of personal admiration by the authors. The specific epithet 
<taxonomicName id="4C6831D2FFFD2012FD97FF25FD76FF16" authorityName="Ngiam &amp; Orr" authorityYear="2017" box="[516,661,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Aeshnidae" genus="Oligoaeschna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sirindhornae">
<emphasis id="B91C9643FFFD2012FD97FF25FD76FF16" box="[516,661,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">sirindhornae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a noun in the genitive case.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37219DAFFFD2017FF54FEF9FB1DFC6E" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="199" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD74A51FFFD2012FF54FEF9FEC6FDF9" blockId="1.[151,1436,151,536]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">
<emphasis id="B91C9643FFFD2012FF54FEF9FE00FEF2" bold="true" box="[199,483,259,284]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">
Description of 
<typeStatus id="54D3F4F3FFFD2012FEE6FEFEFE3DFEF2" box="[373,478,260,284]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B91C9643FFFD2012FE79FEFEFDC4FEF3" box="[490,551,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">Head</emphasis>
. Labium almost entirely brown and broad basally; labial palps generally brown and slightly darkened apically. Labrum dark brown, its lower part black laterally. Mandibles black. Anteclypeus dark brown. Postclypeus dark brown with the upper half much darker. Frons entirely black except for a slight yellowish horizontal stripe on both sides. In dorsal view frons moderately produced with corners and anterior margin rounded (
<figureCitation id="135356D4FFFD2012FECBFE6EFE79FE42" box="[344,410,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,244,1544,1566]" captionTargetBox="[201,1378,614,1501]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[162,1426,580,1534]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Oligaeschna sirindhorni sp. nov. holotype,habitus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1064486/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
); margin with dense fringe of moderately long setae. Antennae black. Vertex shiny yellow, rectangular with rounded corners. Ocelli pale yellowish. Occiput entirely black except for two pale yellowish horizontal stripes, one on each sides of lower half occiput the occiput lower half. Eyes typical of the genus; dark green in life.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF171AD9FFFD2012FF04F9F2FCE2F9F0" box="[151,769,1544,1566]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1064486/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" targetBox="[201,1378,614,1501]" targetPageId="1">
<paragraph id="8BD74A51FFFD2012FF04F9F2FCE2F9F0" blockId="1.[151,769,1544,1566]" box="[151,769,1544,1566]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">
<emphasis id="B91C9643FFFD2012FF04F9F2FEEFF9F0" bold="true" box="[151,268,1544,1566]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">FIGURE 1.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C6831D2FFFD2012FE81F9F2FE1EF9F0" authority="Ngiam &amp; Orr, 2017" authorityName="Ngiam &amp; Orr" authorityYear="2017" box="[274,509,1544,1566]" class="Insecta" family="Aeshnidae" genus="Oligaeschna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sirindhorni" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B91C9643FFFD2012FE81F9F2FE1EF9F0" box="[274,509,1544,1566]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">Oligaeschna sirindhorni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22F2B38FFFD2012FD90F9F2FDACF9F0" box="[515,591,1544,1566]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B91C9643FFFD2012FD90F9F2FDACF9F0" bold="true" box="[515,591,1544,1566]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
holotype, habitus.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BD74A51FFFD2012FF54F9B9FAC6F926" blockId="1.[151,1437,1603,1880]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">
<emphasis id="B91C9643FFFD2012FF54F9B9FEFBF9B2" box="[199,280,1603,1628]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">Thorax</emphasis>
. Prothorax almost entirely black. Synthorax black with greenish dorsal stripes angled inwards on the mesepisternum, and transverse greenish stripes below the pre-alar ridge. Greenish spots present on the mesoscutum, mesopostnotum, metascutum, metascutellum, and humeral and axillary sclerites of all wings. Laterally (
<figureCitation id="135356D4FFFD2012FE98F955FEBEF926" box="[267,349,1711,1736]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,244,1121,1143]" captionTargetBox="[232,1358,209,1057]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[208,1376,195,1101]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Oligaeschna sirindhornae sp. nov. holotype: a. synthorax lateral view; b. anal appendages, dorsal view; c anal appendages, lateralview; d. detail of penisshowing absenceof flagellum on terminal segment." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1064488/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">Fig. 2a</figureCitation>
), greenish stripe on the mesepimeron; metepimeron almost entirely green. Legs black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD74A51FFFD2012FF54F92FFC06F8B6" blockId="1.[151,1437,1603,1880]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">
<emphasis id="B91C9643FFFD2012FF54F92FFEE9F902" box="[199,266,1749,1772]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">Wings</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="135356D4FFFD2012FE89F929FEBDF902" box="[282,350,1747,1772]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="2.[151,244,2003,2025]" captionTargetBox="[178,1409,1237,1953]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[164,1423,1220,1982]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 3. Oligaeschna sirindhornae sp.nov. holotype:wing venation." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1064490/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Fw with 17 antenodal cross-veins (Anx) and nine postnodal cross-veins (Pnx). Pterostigma (Pt) dark, overlaying three cells. Two cubital cross veins (Cux). In Hw, 13 antenodal and 11 postnodal cross-veins. Pt dark, overlaying three and a half cells. Two Cux. Three cells in anal triangle and three cells in anal loop. Three cells in the triangle in both wings, membranule in both wings small, dark brown.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF171AD9FFFE2011FF04FB9BFBC6FB7A" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1064488/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="197" targetBox="[232,1358,209,1057]" targetPageId="2">
